==Abstract==

This IIP describes transaction relay using witness transaction IDs (wtxids) instead of txids. It is adapted from BIP 339 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Txids do not commit to witness data, allowing third-party malleability. Using wtxids for relay:
* Prevents orphan transaction issues from malleated witnesses
* Enables more efficient compact block reconstruction
* Simplifies transaction tracking

==Specification==

===wtxidrelay Message===

<pre>
wtxidrelay: (empty)
</pre>

Sent during handshake before "verack" to indicate wtxid relay preference.

===Behavior Changes===

When wtxidrelay is negotiated:

# INV messages use MSG_WTX (0x05) instead of MSG_TX (0x01)
# GETDATA uses MSG_WTX for transaction requests
# Transaction tracking uses wtxid keys

===WTXID Calculation===

<pre>
wtxid = SHA3-256(serialized_transaction_with_witness)
txid  = SHA3-256(serialized_transaction_without_witness)
</pre>

For transactions without witness data, wtxid equals txid.

===Inventory Types===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Value !! Description
|-
| MSG_TX || 1 || Transaction by txid
|-
| MSG_WTX || 5 || Transaction by wtxid
|}

